%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECondie%20(second%20from%20left)%20was%20promoted%20to%20CEO%20at%20Shieldpay%20in%202024.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Sophie%20Condie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESophie%20Condie%20is%20a%20mom%20of%20three.%20In%202024%2C%20she%20was%20promoted%20to%20CEO%20at%20the%20fintech%20company%20Shieldpay.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20was%20concerned%20the%20promotion%20would%20impact%20her%20kids%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20has%20a%20genetic%20brain%20disorder.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECondie%20said%20being%20a%20CEO%20is%20challenging%2C%20but%20raising%20a%20disabled%20child%20has%20made%20her%20better%20at%20her%20job.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Sophie%20Condie%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20fintech%20company%20Shieldpay%2C%20from%20England.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20mother%2C%20but%20I%20never%20thought%20I'd%20be%20a%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20three%20kids%2C%20who%20are%20eleven%2C%20eight%2C%20and%20four%2C%20and%20I'm%20also%20the%20CEO%20of%20Shieldpay%2C%20a%20UK-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F49-most-promising-fintech-startups-according-top-vc-investors-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efintech%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20child%2C%20Reuben%2C%20has%20a%20rare%20genetic%20brain%20disorder%20called%20Joubert%20syndrome.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20I%20considered%20being%20a%20full-time%20mom%20and%20carer%2C%20but%20I%20needed%20the%20pace%20and%20demands%20of%20working.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaising%20a%20child%20with%20a%20disability%20has%20taught%20me%20a%20new%20level%20of%20resilience%2C%20and%20it's%20helped%20me%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-be-a-great-ceo-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebe%20a%20better%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce99dfc6-cf9c-47ae-bb5e-e3cedab55cd9%5C%22%3EBeing%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20wasn't%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20my%20husband%20when%20I%20was%2025.%20When%20we%20started%20talking%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwanted-to-be-a-millionaire-before-i-started-having-kids-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehaving%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20made%20it%20clear%20I%20wanted%20to%20have%20my%20career%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20Reuben%20in%202013%2C%20when%20I'd%20already%20been%20in%20banking%20for%20roughly%20seven%20years.%20After%20he%20was%20born%2C%20we%20found%20out%20he%20had%20Joubert%20syndrome%2C%20which%20affects%20his%20breathing%20and%20muscles.%20He's%20non-verbal%2C%20non-mobile%2C%20and%20tube-fed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20shared%20the%20childcare%20and%20also%20employed%20a%20carer%20for%20Reuben.%20When%20he%20was%20around%20three%2C%20I%20left%20my%20banking%20job%20and%20took%20just%20under%20a%20year%20off%20to%20care%20for%20Reuben%20and%20for%20some%20other%20family%20members%20who%20had%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20considered%20becoming%20a%20full-time%20mom%20because%20Reuben%20needed%20me%2C%20and%20it%20would%20make%20sense%20if%20we%20had%20more%20children.%20After%20having%20my%20second%20child%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20for%20my%20own%20mental%20health.%20I%20couldn't%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-job-stay-at-home-mom-parenting-hard-work-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estay-at-home%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20carer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20got%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsandwich-generation-caregiving-minimum-wage-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull-time%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20support%20so%20I%20could%20go%20back%20to%20work%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20was%20supportive.%20In%202017%2C%20I%20joined%20Form3%2C%20a%20fintech%20company.%20I%20adored%20the%20pace%20and%20demands%20of%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c5cd3f3-89ff-4e46-982d-6f3d3dfa23dd%5C%22%3EI%20was%20concerned%20about%20how%20becoming%20a%20CEO%20would%20impact%20my%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20having%20my%20third%20child%20in%202021%2C%20I%20started%20thinking%20about%20my%20next%20career%20move.%20I%20joined%20Shieldpay%20as%20an%20operations%20director.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20I%20was%20made%20COO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20the%20company%20went%20through%20a%20restructure%2C%20and%20I%20was%20appointed%20as%20the%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20promotion%20happened%20quickly.%20I%20thought%20hard%20about%20how%20it%20could%20impact%20our%20family%2C%20but%20my%20husband%20encouraged%20me%20to%20take%20the%20role.%20My%20first%20task%20as%20CEO%20was%20implementing%20the%20restructure%20%E2%80%94%20a%20baptism%20of%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20I%20started%2C%20my%20daughter%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20the%20No.%201%20boss%20now%2C%20not%20just%20No.%202.%26quot%3B%20I%20asked%20how%20that%20made%20her%20feel%2C%20and%20she%20said%20it%20was%20a%20good%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20she%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20you%20to%20be%20the%20No.%201%20boss%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20opportunity%20to%20talk%20to%20her%20about%20the%20situation.%20My%20focus%20was%20split%20across%20many%20things%2C%20so%20I%20was%20probably%20more%20distracted%20than%20I%20realized%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f6ae6d3-34c4-4f9e-9856-e5840df25790%5C%22%3EI%20have%20big%20ambitions%20for%20our%20company%2C%20but%20I%20know%20it's%20not%20a%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20taking%20the%20CEO%20role%2C%20the%20work%20has%20been%20harder%2C%20and%20I've%20put%20more%20expectations%20on%20myself.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20COO%2C%20I%20was%