his%20success%20should%20be%20your%20merit%20%E2%80%94%20incomparable%20and%20self-motivating.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFloods%20of%20change%3A%20Early%20writing%20days%20and%20struggles%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20a%20child%2C%20there%20were%20floods%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F400833%2Fpayal-kumar-feed-the-souls-ngo-delhi-slums-education-skill-training-for-women%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMadanmohantala%20slum%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20was%20back%20in%201989%2C%20if%20I%20recall%20correctly%20when%20I%20was%20in%20class%204.%20The%20water%20levels%20kept%20rising%2C%20so%20we%20had%20to%20vacate.%20We%20went%20to%20my%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20place%20to%20live%20for%20a%20while.%20I%20was%20an%20introvert%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20read%20something%2C%20and%20I%20used%20to%20live%20in%20my%20world%20of%20imagination.%20While%20I%20was%20taking%20a%20stroll%20outside%20the%20house%2C%20I%20found%20a%20book%20under%20a%20tree.%20It%20had%20dust%20on%20it%2C%20and%20the%20corners%20were%20damaged.%20This%20book%20was%20a%20collection%20of%20short%20stories%2C%20and%20I%20started%20reading%20them%2C%20one%20after%20the%20other.%20And%20that%20is%20when%20it%20occurred%20to%20me%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20%3Cem%3Elekhak%20(writer)%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3Esays%20Pintu%2C%20who%20asked%20us%20to%20wait%20for%20five%20minutes%20as%20he%20was%20applying%20%3Cem%3Echoon%20%3C%2Fem%3Eon%20some%20betel%20nuts%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20phone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPintu%20was%20studying%20at%20%3Cem%3EBarisha%20Jankalyan%20Vidyapeeth%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20though%20his%20parents%20were%20daily%20wage%20workers%20and%20had%20to%20feed%20their%20family%2C%20Pintu%20never%20let%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F363045%2Fgrassroots-organisations-initiatives-changemakers-teach-education-underprivileged-children-slum%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoverty%3C%2Fa%3E%20shadow%20his%20dream%20of%20studying%20while%20also%20taking%20up%20odd%20jobs%20so%20that%20his%20education%20would%20never%20burden%20his%20family.%20He%20even%20went%20on%20to%20collect%20and%20read%20books%20that%20used%20to%20be%20given%20to%20%3Cem%3Ekabadiwalas%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ragpickers)%20as%20%3Cem%3Eraddi%20(paper%20waste).%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20discovering%20my%20fondness%20for%20writing%2C%20I%20never%20kept%20my%20pen%20down%20and%20when%20I%20was%20in%20eighth%20grade%2C%20I%20saw%20an%20advertisement%20in%20the%20newspaper%20that%20read%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Geetikar%20Chahi!%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20which%20translates%20to%20%E2%80%98Songwriter%20wanted!%E2%80%99%20I%20thought%20that%20this%20would%20be%20my%20breakthrough.%20I%20already%20had%20a%20collection%20of%20self-composed%20songs%20and%20poems%20by%201993%2C%20as%20I%20started%20writing%20back%20in%201989.%20After%20collecting%20Rs%2010-15%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20address%2C%20and%20the%20advertiser%20took%20a%20look%20at%20my%20songs%20and%20told%20me%20that%20he%20would%20take%20two%20songs%20and%20charge%20%3Cem%3Eme%20%3C%2Fem%3ERs%20600.%20My%20heart%20shattered%20into%20pieces%20as%20my%20whole%20family%E2%80%99s%20income%20for%20a%20month%20would%20be%20Rs%20300.%20However%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20it%20was%20a%20fraud%2C%20so%20I%20came%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20shared%20Pintu.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-49-1751956541.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22With%20just%20Rs%201500%2C%20Pintu%20Pohan%20started%20his%20Paanwala%20dukaan%20around%201999.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.th